title: Taj Mahal (1968) - FLAC
description: Taj Mahal's first album released in 1968.  His band featured Jessie Ed Davis and Ry Cooder alternating on lead guitar. a strong mix of originals, R&B standards, and quite possibly, the definitive interpretation of Robert Johnson's "Walking Blues" closing out this tremendous debut set.  Cream may have boasted they were "blues ancient and modern," but Taj Mahal is a far more appropriate fit to rhat description.  Enjoy
